{
  "stem": "6736.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I wouldn't stay in the farm for the holiday, so I went into the city to pray in the city.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Neustadt.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then I went between the Rosh Hashanah, Yom Kippur, back to the farmer.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the farmer said, if you're that religious of a Jew, I'm afraid to keep you.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But Yom Kippur I would anyway and not stay with him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I went back on Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "A few days later-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in the meantime, while all those months were going by, they start taking the people away from Miedzyrzec.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they took-- they start taking them I don't know where, but--",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But my parents couldn't stand there, because there was over-- no food.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So my father got, got dressed up like a, a peasant.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They, they, they told me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm going to tell you.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father went to his brother to Ozarow.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my mother put on a handkerchief like a peasant girl, with five children went to the ghetto Krakow.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She went by train.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She bought tickets on the train.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She said that she was a refugee from Poznan.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she lost her husband in the war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my father had some papers.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I don't think my mother had any papers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But when she came to the ghetto-- we had a central, like a post place.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My uncle Isaac Levenstein, his wife Sally, and two children lived in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So we wrote to them, and they wrote, so that's how we communicate with each other.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But my mother couldn't go in to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They wouldn't let her in with five children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So she went by horse and wagon to a town near Krakow.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It was called Proszowice.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "In Proszowice, we had-- my father had a very good friend.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
